cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DB 

The paper is about designing a recommendation system using collaborative filtering, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed model, Multi-Matrix Factorization (MMF), is a machine learning model that falls under the category of supervised learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the item cold-start problem, which is a common issue in recommender systems and falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on real datasets, which involves data management and analysis, falling under the category of databases (cs.DB).
